---
import DscrCalculator from "@/components/calculators/DscrCalculator";
import ToolShell from "@/components/dscr/ToolShell.astro";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What is commercial DSCR for multifamily?",
    a: "Commercial DSCR measures whether normalized NOI covers annual debt service (principal and interest). Lenders on 5+ unit properties use DSCR with debt yield and LTV to size proceeds—not residential 1–4 unit DSCR programs.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do you calculate DSCR?",
    a: "DSCR = NOI ÷ Annual Debt Service. If NOI is $960,000 and annual P&I is $720,000, DSCR is 1.33x. Higher coverage generally supports more proceeds or better pricing.",
  },
  {
    q: "What DSCR do multifamily lenders require?",
    a: "Requirements vary by product and asset stage. Many stabilized agency deals target roughly 1.20x–1.30x on in-place NOI, while bridge lenders may accept lower in-place coverage if a credible stabilization plan exists.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my DSCR differ from the lender's?",
    a: "Lenders may haircut revenue, stress expenses, include reserves, and use their own rate and amortization assumptions. Sponsor spreadsheet DSCR often runs higher than lender underwriting DSCR.",
  },
  {
    q: "Does interest-only debt affect DSCR?",
    a: "Yes. IO periods reduce near-term debt service, which can inflate DSCR temporarily. Lenders often also test amortizing DSCR or debt yield to avoid over-leveraging into IO structures.",
  },
  {
    q: "How can I improve DSCR before refinancing?",
    a: "Focus on durable NOI improvements—occupancy, effective rent, expense control—and realistic loan sizing. Short-term rate bets rarely substitute for stronger operating performance.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is this calculator for residential DSCR loans?",
    a: "No. Multi-Family USA focuses on commercial multifamily financing for 5+ unit apartment buildings. Residential 1–4 unit DSCR products follow different guidelines—use the <a href=\"https://dscrauthority.com/tools/dscr-calculator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">free DSCR calculator</a> on our sister site DSCR Authority.",
  },
];
---

<ToolShell
  title="DSCR Calculator for Commercial Multifamily | Multi-Family USA"
  description="Free commercial DSCR calculator for 5+ unit multifamily loans. Stress-test debt service coverage with formulas, FAQs, and a worked apartment example."
  h1="Commercial DSCR Calculator"
  toolSlug="commercial-dscr-calculator"
  tagline="Stress-test debt service coverage for commercial apartment buildings—not residential 1–4 unit DSCR programs."
  keywords={["dscr calculator", "commercial dscr", "multifamily dscr", "debt service coverage", "apartment loan qualification"]}
  relatedGuides={["commercial-dscr-explained", "debt-yield-and-ltv-framework", "multifamily-underwriting-basics"]}
  relatedComparisons={["agency-vs-bridge", "fixed-vs-floating-rate"]}
  relatedLoanTypes={["agency-stabilized", "bridge-value-add"]}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <Fragment slot="calculator">
    <DscrCalculator client:load />
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
      <h2>How to calculate commercial DSCR</h2>
      <p>
        For multifamily acquisitions and refinances on 5+ units, commercial DSCR is:
      </p>
      <p><strong>DSCR = NOI ÷ Annual Debt Service</strong></p>
      <p>
        Annual debt service includes principal and interest (and sometimes lender-required reserves). Use normalized NOI consistent with lender underwriting, not unadjusted sponsor projections.
      </p>

      <h2>Worked example: 32-unit value-add acquisition</h2>
      <p>
        A sponsor acquires a 32-unit value-add property. In-place normalized NOI is <strong>$480,000</strong>. Proposed permanent debt service is <strong>$380,000</strong> per year at full amortization.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>In-place DSCR: $480,000 ÷ $380,000 = <strong>1.26x</strong></li>
        <li>Stabilized NOI target of $620,000 implies <strong>1.63x</strong> coverage on the same debt service</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Bridge lenders may size on in-place metrics while agency takeout lenders focus on stabilized coverage. See our <a href="/learn/commercial-dscr-explained">commercial DSCR guide</a> and <a href="/compare/agency-vs-bridge">agency vs bridge comparison</a>. For 1–4 unit rentals, use the <a href="https://dscrauthority.com/tools/dscr-calculator/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">free DSCR calculator</a> at DSCR Authority instead.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Fragment>
</ToolShell>
